Bundled Font Licenses
=====================

This directory contains subset fonts used for PDF signature visual
appearances. Only the glyphs needed for signature fields are included.


Noto Sans (NotoSans-Subset.ttf)
--------------------------------
Source:     NotoSans-Regular.ttf + NotoSansArmenian-Regular.ttf
            Google Noto Fonts (https://fonts.google.com/noto)
Copyright:  2012 Google Inc. All Rights Reserved.
License:    SIL Open Font License, Version 1.1 (https://openfontlicense.org)

The OFL permits use, modification, and redistribution (including in
binary/embedded form) provided the fonts are not sold by themselves.
Full license: https://github.com/notofonts/noto-fonts/blob/main/LICENSE


GHEA Grapalat (GHEAGrapalat-Subset.ttf)
-----------------------------------------
Source:     GHEAGrapalat-Regular.ttf
Designer:   Edik Ghabuzyan (2008), National Book Chamber of Armenia
Copyright:  "Armenian National Grapalat" SNCO (National Book Chamber),
            a state non-commercial organization of the Republic of Armenia.

Legal basis:
  Government of the Republic of Armenia, Decree N 1259-N,
  adopted September 24, 2010, effective October 8, 2010.
  Signed by Prime Minister Tigran Sargsyan.

  Official title (Armenian):
    "Hayastani Hanrapetutyan petakan pashtonakan p'astatghtashrjanarhutyan
    mej kirarhman hamar partadir haykakan hamakargchayin taratesaktner
    hastatelu masin"
  (On Establishing Armenian Computer Fonts Mandatory for Use in RA State
  Official Document Circulation)

  Sources:
    - ARLIS (Armenian Legal Information System): docid=61217
      https://www.arlis.am/DocumentView.aspx?docid=61217
    - e-gov.am: decree item 18506
      https://www.e-gov.am/gov-decrees/item/18506
    - Full text (PDF):
      https://www.e-gov.am/u_files/file/decrees/kar/2010/09/10_1259.pdf

  Article 2 of the decree declares both fonts property of the Republic
  of Armenia and grants unrestricted free use to all natural persons
  (individuals) and legal entities in electronic information and
  communication systems.

  The decree was adopted with reference to the provisions of the RA Law
  on Copyrights.

No standardized open-source license (SIL OFL, MIT, etc.) is attached.
The legal basis for redistribution is the government decree granting
unrestricted free use in electronic information systems.


GHEA Mariam (GHEAMariam-Subset.ttf)
-------------------------------------
Source:     GHEAMariamReg.otf
Designer:   Edik Ghabuzyan (2008), National Book Chamber of Armenia
Copyright:  "Armenian National Grapalat" SNCO (National Book Chamber),
            a state non-commercial organization of the Republic of Armenia.

Legal basis:
  Same as GHEA Grapalat above (Decree N 1259-N, September 24, 2010).
  Article 2 grants the same unrestricted free use rights.
